                        <h2><strong>Perimeter Calculator</strong></h2>

<p>Our perimeter calculator helps you to determine the perimeter for severa=
l geometrical shapes with different parameters. Well, how to find perimeter=
 of different shapes is no more complex with our free perimeter to area cal=
culator.</p>

<h2><strong>What is Perimeter?</strong></h2>

<p>In mathematics, the perimeter of a shape is defined as the total distanc=
e around the shape. Basically, it is the length of any shape, as long as it=
 is expanded linearly. The range of various shapes can be the same in lengt=
h according to their size.</p>

<h2><strong>How to Find the Perimeter?</strong></h2>

<p>Usually, the simplest and most straightforward method is to sum all side=
s of the shape. However, sometimes there are no edges (such as ellipses, ci=
rcles, etc.) or one or more edges are unknown. Below are some perimeter equ=
ations used with the perimeter calculator to determine the perimeter.</p>

<h3><strong>Perimeter of a Square:</strong></h3>

<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">A square has all sides of equal length=
. To calculate its perimeter, multiply the length of all these sides by 4.<=
/span></p>

<p><img a=3D"" alt=3D"perimeter of a square" height=3D"120px" src=3D"https:=
//calculator-online.net/images/Sqaure%20(axa).webp" width=3D"120px"></p>

<p><strong class=3D"bg-gray px-1">Perimeter of a Square =3D a + a + a + a =
=3D 4a</strong></p>

<h3><strong>Perimeter of a Rectangle:</strong></h3>

<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">The </span>rectangular perimeter<span =
style=3D"font-weight: 400;"> is the total distance around its outer boundar=
y. It is the same as the perimeter of a square, but the difference is two p=
airs of equal-length sides in a rectangle.</span></p>

<p><img a=3D"" alt=3D"perimeter of a rectangle" height=3D"120px" src=3D"htt=
ps://calculator-online.net/images/Rectangle%20(axb).webp" width=3D"140px"><=
/p>

<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;"><b class=3D"bg-gray px-1">Perimeter of=
 a Rectangle =3D 2 =C3=97 (Length + Width)</b></span></p>

<h3><strong>Perimeter of a Triangle:</strong></h3>

<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">The </span>perimeter of a triangle<spa=
n style=3D"font-weight: 400;"> is the total length of its three sides. So, =
find it by adding all these sides:</span></p>

<p><img a=3D"" alt=3D"perimeter of a triangle" height=3D"120px" src=3D"http=
s://calculator-online.net/images/Triangle.webp" width=3D"120px"></p>

<p><strong class=3D"bg-gray px-1">Perimeter of a Triangle =3D a + b + c&nbs=
p;</strong></p>

<h3><strong>Perimeter of a Circle:</strong></h3>

<p><span style=3D"font-weight: 400;">The </span>perimeter of a circle<span =
